Package: rase
Title: Range Ancestral State Estimation for Phylogeography and Comparative Analyses
Version: 0.3-2
Date: 2017-03-21
Authors@R: c(person("Ignacio", "Quintero", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "ignacio.quintero@yale.edu"),
			person("Forrest W.", "Crawford", role = "aut", email = "forrest.crawford@yale.edu"),
			person("Petr", "Keil", role = "aut", email = "petrkeil@seznam.cz"))
Depends: R (>= 2.14.0), ape (>= 3.1-0), polyCub (>= 0.5-0), spatstat (>= 1.36-0)
Imports: mvtnorm (>= 1.0-0), rgl, sm, methods, grDevices, stats,
Suggests: sp, coda, rpanel
Description: Implements the Range Ancestral State Estimation for phylogeography described in Quintero, I., Keil, P., Jetz, W., & Crawford, F. W. (2015) <DOI:https://doi.org/10.1093/sysbio/syv057>. It also includes Bayesian inference of ancestral states under a Brownian Motion model of character evolution and Maximum Likelihood estimation of rase for n-dimensional data. Visualizing functions in 3D are implemented using the rgl package.
License: GPL (>=2)
